 (LBV) stars. In addition, we propose that the presence and strength of\nthe newly reported Mg II lines might be used as a new complementary criterion\nto identify LBV candidates. The spectra of the other two objects imply that MN\n108 is an O-type supergiant, whereas MN 109 could be an LBV candidate in its\nactive phase. We derive lower limits for the reddening toward the stars and\nfind that three of all de-reddened fall into the region of confirmed LBVs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Aug 2020 13:54:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-30"}
