e youngest\nsince there is no correlation between electron densities and the H$\\beta$\nluminosities. The strong correlation found between L$_{H\\beta}$-L$_{[O III]}$\nimplies that the so far not understood cut off of the planetary luminosity\nfunction (PNLF) based on [O III] magnitudes can be investigated using\nL$_{H\\beta}$, a parameter much easier to study.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Aug 2020 15:20:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Aug 2020 07:18:38 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 27 Aug 2020 05:54:11 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 4 Sep 2020 06:45:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-09"}
